This paper deals with graph neural networks, which are a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on the ability of these networks to handle dynamic, or online, data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper mentions conducting experiments on limited amounts of data, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories.
